\cb5 An \'93eigenvector\'94 is an input that doesn\'92t change direction when it\'92s run through the matrix (it points \'93along the axis\'94). And although the direction doesn\'92t change, the size might. The eigenvalue is the amount the eigenvector is scaled up or down when going through the matrix.\cb1 \
